Readme
======

This is my own (CoffeeScript) interpretation to the work that pshved did:
http://coldattic.info/shvedsky/pro/blogs/a-foo-walks-into-a-bar/posts/98
I'd recommmend a look at his blog post about what sign to use and other hardware tips.

Depedencies
----------
* Perl
	libdevice-serialport-perl

* download Device-MiniLED:
	http://search.cpan.org/~kschwab/Device-MiniLED/
* install Device-MiniLED
        perl Build.PL
        ./Build
        ./Build test
        ./Build install

* npm depedencies:
	async
	request
	underscore
	xml2js
	line-by-line


Config
---------
    config.json file in the format of:
    ```
        {
            "weather": {
                "key": ""
            },
            "birthdays": [
                {
                    "name": "",
                    "day": 1,
                    "month": 1
                }
            ]
        }
    ```
